  "@type": "Capability",
  "critical": false,
  "description": "Raising domesticated pigs (Sus scrofa domesticus) for pork, lard, and waste disposal. Pigs convert feed to carcass more efficiently than cattle or sheep (70-80% dressed yield), consume food waste and crop residues other livestock reject, and produce 8-12 piglets per litter. The most productive omnivore in the livestock stable.",
  "early_win": true,
  "early_win_note": "Market weight (90-110 kg) at 5-7 months. Pigs convert kitchen waste and crop residues into meat and lard, closing the food waste loop.",
